  "text": "While resulting in many improved physical properties, an increase in DC will also increase the polymerization shrinkage stress with an adverse effect on marginal leakage. Therefore, several workers have recommended that the DC be increased to a percentage that balances optimum physical properties with polymerization shrinkage [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] .",
